-- Rexel launches official bid for Hagemeyer
-- 
-- Fri Dec 21, 2007 1:24am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/21/us-hagemeyer-rexel-idUSWEB112620071221

 

 AMSTERDAM  (Reuters) - Rexel ( RXL.PA ), the world's biggest electrical parts distributor, officially launched on Friday its 3.1 billion euro ($4.45 billion) or 4.85 euros per share bid for Dutch rival Hagemeyer HAGN.AS. 

 Rexel, which will sell certain Hagemeyer operations to French unlisted peer Sonepar, said in a statement in Dutch daily Financieele Dagblad it will also sell its present activities in Germany to Sonepar and buy Sonepar's Swedish activities. (Reporting by  Gilbert Kreijger )